Any GC class <-> Any OSConfig module MIM

GC class equivalent to MIM object
GC parameter equivalent to MIM setting
Each class can have up to 30 parameters
Parameters can be of type string, integer, or boolean.

For OSCOnfig, each GC parameter needs to describe the following:

The MIM component name.
The MIM object name.
The MIM object value (payload containing the object's settings values).

WHAT IF EACH POLICY TARGETS ONE OSCONFIG MODULE?
Then the GC class can be described by 3 string parameters: MIM component namne, MIM object name, MIM object value
How many such classes to have as MIM component can contain several MIM objects?
DeviceInfo has 1 component and 15 reported objects for example.

A MIM that describes a GC class:

Variant A (all class parameters at once):

1 component
1 reported object with 90 reported settings (3 types x 30 parameters) <<< does not matter if we combine the settings in one object payload value (string)
1 desired object with 90 desired settings

Variant B (one class parameter at a time - this may restrict classes to only one parameter):

1 component
1 reported object with 3 reported settings
1 desired object with 3 desired settings


